name: Tradesman 100 Portable Forced Air
short_description:
Engineered to deliver reliable, directional heat, L.B. White Tradesman heaters feature a unique 3-trial ignition system, the industry's heaviest gauge combustion chamber and burner plate, and Self Diagnostic Service Saver models for convenient trouble-shooting. L.B. White has perfected every aspect of our construction heaters design to withstand the harsh working environments.
  • Dependable electronic spark ignition
  • Superior Tri-Shield finish provides extended protection against abrasion and corrosion.
  • Thermostatic temperature control (170 and 400 models)
  • Adjustable front leg provides easy direction of heat (170 model)
  • Variable output saves fuel
  • 100% test fired at our plant
  • Direct-fired = 99.97% fuel efficiency
  • CSA US and Canadian

name: Workman 100 - Standard LP
short_description:
These standard duty convection heaters feature adjustable output control to save fuel, and a unique top design for superior heat distribution. Workman heaters provide 360° heating and don't require electricity.
  • LP and NG Models available
  • Lightweight for easy maneuverability
  • Piezo pilot ignition
  • Direct-fired = 99.97% fuel efficiency
  • Enclosed stainless steel burner provides superior wind resistance
  • 360° heat output
  • One piece barrel, no assembly required
  • CSA US and Canada

name: Circulating Heater
short_description:
Designed for large, open-air area heating, L.B. White circulating heaters provide large Btu/h outputs using unique rugged steel case designs, and include powerful paddle-blade fans and cast-iron burners to circulate high volumes of heated air easily and effectively.

Strong, durable and designed to withstand long hours of operation, L.B. White circulating heaters are ideal for large space heating such as docks, warehouse openings, concrete drying, or brickwork. All Jet, Twin Jet, and Big Bertha natural gas or liquid propane gas heaters feature pilot ignition for dependable starts, as well as standard or optional thermostatic controls for automated temperature management.

name: Director Ductable Heater
short_description:
The vented Director heater is ideal for providing dry, clean heat into insulated spaces, work areas, heating docks or anywhere 100% clean air is needed. L.B. White's ductable Director heater features a fuel-saving high efficiency heat exchanger, high capacity fuel tank, and pre-heated fuel filter. L.B. White has perfected every aspect of our construction heaters design to withstand the harsh working environments.
  • 300,000 Btu/h models
  • Kerosene, #1 diesel or #1 fuel oil
  • Easy to transport
  • High efficiency heat exchanger saves fuel
  • Dependable, electronic spark ignition
  • High capacity fuel tank
  • Pre-heated fuel filter standard
  • Rugged, semi-pneumatic wheels for better maneuverability
  • Remote thermostatic control available
  • 100% test fired at our plant
  • Water resistant control box
  • Optional rain cap
  • Optional steel exhaust pipe extension gets exhaust away from the work area
  • Automatic fuel shut-off
  • CSA USA and Canada
